author: VR Gorilla - Virtual Reality & 360 Videos
description:
Welcome to The Keukenhof, one of the largest flower gardens in the world, most famous for its abundance of tulips. The park covers an area of almost 80 acres, with approximately 7 million flower bulbs planted each year.
 
The Keukenhof is open for eight weeks, from mid-March to mid-May, with mid-April generally being the best time to see the tulips in full bloom. It’s a brief window to witness such a spectacular display, so every visit feels truly special.
title: The Keukenhof the 'Garden of Europe' in the Netherlands - Virtual Travel - 8K 360 3D
